When trying to set a start date for a version in GH (planning board or chart board), following error is thrown:
{noformat}
Invalid format: &amp;quot;25.08.2010&amp;quot; is malformed at &amp;quot;.08.2010&amp;quot;
{noformat}
See also screenshot: error-after-setting-startdate-in-gh.png

Date/time configuration is changed to match DE/AT standards. I have attached screenshot from Jira Admin area and the jira.property file (datetime-config-in-jiraui-and-property-file.png)

GreenHopper creates internally used custom fields if required, storing the field ID to check for existence. Custom field IDs are prefixed with "customfield_". GreenHopper uses uppercase comparison, but under a Turkish locale the lowercase 'i' will not convert into uppercase 'I'.

The result is an exception on every page in GreenHopper, since the custom field for Release Version History can't be found. Additionally, the custom field will be created over and over again, since GreenHopper believes it not to be there.

{code}
Exception caught in 500 page com.pyxis.greenhopper.jira.fields.NotSupported cannot be cast to com.pyxis.greenhopper.jira.fields.CustomFieldMultiVersion
java.lang.ClassCastException: com.pyxis.greenhopper.jira.fields.NotSupported cannot be cast to com.pyxis.greenhopper.jira.fields.CustomFieldMultiVersion
{code}

When I run the following query on Issue Navigator:

{quote}project = "Project A" AND "Force Rank" > 100 ORDER BY "Force Rank" ASC{quote} 

It displays all issues from Project A.

When I run

{quote}project = "Project A" AND "Force Rank" < 100 ORDER BY "Force Rank" ASC{quote}

Or 

{quote}project = "Project A" AND "Force Rank" < 100000 ORDER BY "Force Rank" ASC{quote}


In both cases, none of the issues from Project A are displayed

And when I run

{quote}project = "Project A" AND "Force Rank" < 100000000000 ORDER BY "Force Rank" ASC{quote}

All issues from Project A are displayed.

The value displayed is actually much higher in the database. Is it possible to save a smaller value in the database?

When I run the following query on Issue Navigator:

{quote}project = "Project A" AND "Force Rank" > 100 ORDER BY "Force Rank" ASC{quote} 

It displays all issues from Project A.

When I run

{quote}project = "Project A" AND "Force Rank" < 100 ORDER BY "Force Rank" ASC{quote}

Or 

{quote}project = "Project A" AND "Force Rank" < 100000 ORDER BY "Force Rank" ASC{quote}


In both cases, none of the issues from Project A are displayed

And when I run

{quote}project = "Project A" AND "Force Rank" < 100000000000 ORDER BY "Force Rank" ASC{quote}

All issues from Project A are displayed.

I understand that the Greenhopper rank field is not really meant to be used outside of greenhopper as it is an internally controlled number, but value displayed is actually much higher in the database. I believe this should be fixed.

This is raised from the [comment|http://confluence.atlassian.com/display/GH/GreenHopper+101?focusedCommentId=223217414#comment-223217414]:

{quote}
I found that when following this 101 on a fresh JIRA install I could not see the 'Compact (Kanban)' view referred to in section'2. Configuring GreenHopper'. However, if you proceed with section '3. Configuring JIRA' and perform the 'Enabling Sub-task' step, this enables the Kanban view.

See also the KB article Compact (Kanban) Option Not Appears in Task Board Views.
{quote}
